The paper describes a knowledge representation and reasoning language based on logic programming, which suggests it could fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), and Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses debugging and profiling tools, which could fall under the categories of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Databases (cs.DB).
